# controversial addition of anchovies but i like it
# the idea here is to create a really smooth cacio e pepe, with very heavy black pepper notes, tbe eventual sauce almost takes on a light earl grey colour from the black pepper water

Create cheese "stock"
Enough for 2 main size serves

250ml full cream milk
100g caciocavallo cheese, chopped 
2 anchovies fillet (can omit)
thermomix 90c 45mins speed 2
Cheese will clump, strain liquid through fine strainer

Toast black pepper (lightly), no oil, add 50ml of pasta water
Most of the compounds is oil soluble, I add water as I want to preserve the black pepper until the cheese comes in

Pasta 3 mins below recommended cooking time, cook with sauce till thick and smooth
Add cheese stock, reduce 2-3 mins, add pasta, cook reduce 5-6 mins
Heat off
25g pecorino finely grated and tossed (optional)
Ensure sauce is smooth
